(6, 4, 6, 'MmWave Technologies and Circuits for RF Systems', NULL, 'Special Session on MmWave Technologies and Circuits for RF Systems\r\n\r\nThis Special session will focus on MmWave design, architectures, technologies, devices, circuits, and systems for RF systems, including low-power radio, phased arrays, beamformers, transceivers and advanced applications targeted for radar, imaging, spectroscopy, and sensing.\r\n\r\nTopics of interests include, but are not limited to, the following:\r\n\r\n Advanced mmWave technologies such as packaging, modelling and testing, EM modelling/co-simulation, advanced integrated MmWave IC, SiP and AiP, etc.\r\n\r\n MmWave passive structures such as transformers, hybrid couplers, filters, baluns, switches, antenna, etc.\r\n\r\n MmWave/RF and front-end circuits such as low noise amplifiers, mixers, mmWave -controlled oscillators, power amplifiers, variable gain amplifiers, etc.\r\n\r\n MmWave architects, systems and subsystems, such as receivers, transmitters, transceivers, phase-locked loops, frequency synthesisers, multistandard transceivers, digital radio, phased array beamformer, etc.\r\n\r\nSpecial Session Co-chairs:\r\n\r\n Nguyen Ngoc Mai Khanh, The University of Tokyo, Japan\r\n\r\n Huynh Phu Minh Cuong, Ho Chi Minh City University of Technology, Vietnam\r\n\r\nSubmission:\r\n\r\n All authors should prepare full versions of papers in Microsoft Word (DOC) or Portable Document Format (PDF). Papers must be limited to six pages, including text, references, tables, and figures  All papers should be prepared according to the IEEE standard template.  Submission link: https://www.edas.info/N29152\r\n\r\nImportant Dates:\r\n\r\n Submissions Deadline: Feb 28th , 2022\r\n\r\n Acceptance Notification: May 10th , 2022\r\n\r\n Camera-ready Version: May 17th, 2022\r\n\r\n Registration Deadline: May 20th, 2022\r\n\r\n Conference Date: July 27th  29th , 2022\r\n\r\nPublication:\r\n\r\nAll accepted papers will be published in the ICCE 2022 Conference Proceedings. Fully accepted papers will be forwarded to be published on IEEE Xplore.', '<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"mso-margin-bottom-alt: auto; line-height: normal; mso-outline-level: 3; background: white;\"><strong><span style=\"font-size: 12.0pt; font-family: \'Arial\',sans-serif; mso-fareast-font-family: \'Times New Roman\'; color: black;\">Special Session on MmWave Technologies and Circuits for RF Systems</span></strong></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"mso-margin-bottom-alt: auto; line-height: normal; background: white;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10.0pt; font-family: \'Arial\',sans-serif; mso-fareast-font-family: \'Times New Roman\'; color: #3b3838; mso-themecolor: background2; mso-themeshade: 64; mso-style-textfill-fill-color: #3B3838; mso-style-textfill-fill-themecolor: background2; mso-style-textfill-fill-alpha: 100.0%; mso-style-textfill-fill-colortransforms: lumm=25000;\">This Special session will focus on MmWave design, architectures, technologies, devices, circuits, and systems for RF systems, including low-power radio, phased arrays, beamformers, transceivers and advanced applications targeted for radar, imaging, spectroscopy, and sensing.</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"mso-margin-bottom-alt: auto; line-height: normal; mso-outline-level: 3; background: white;\"><strong><span style=\"font-size: 12.0pt; font-family: \'Arial\',sans-serif; mso-fareast-font-family: \'Times New Roman\'; color: black;\">Topics of interests include, but are not limited to, the following:</span></strong></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li><span style=\"font-size: 10.0pt; font-family: \'Arial\',sans-serif; mso-fareast-font-family: \'Times New Roman\'; color: #3b3838; mso-themecolor: background2; mso-themeshade: 64; mso-style-textfill-fill-color: #3B3838; mso-style-textfill-fill-themecolor: background2; mso-style-textfill-fill-alpha: 100.0%; mso-style-textfill-fill-colortransforms: lumm=25000;\">Advanced mmWave technologies such as packaging, modelling and testing, EM modelling/co-simulation, advanced integrated MmWave IC, SiP and AiP, etc.<br /><span style=\"font-size: 10.0pt; font-family: \'Arial\',sans-serif; mso-fareast-font-family: \'Times New Roman\'; color: #3b3838; mso-themecolor: background2; mso-themeshade: 64; mso-style-textfill-fill-color: #3B3838; mso-style-textfill-fill-themecolor: background2; mso-style-textfill-fill-alpha: 100.0%; mso-style-textfill-fill-colortransforms: lumm=25000;\">MmWave passive structures such as transformers, hybrid couplers, filters, baluns, switches, antenna, etc.</span></span></li>\r\n<li><span style=\"font-size: 10.0pt; font-family: \'Arial\',sans-serif; mso-fareast-font-family: \'Times New Roman\'; color: #3b3838; mso-themecolor: background2; mso-themeshade: 64; mso-style-textfill-fill-color: #3B3838; mso-style-textfill-fill-themecolor: background2; mso-style-textfill-fill-alpha: 100.0%; mso-style-textfill-fill-colortransforms: lumm=25000;\">MmWave/RF and front-end circuits such as low noise amplifiers, mixers, mmWave -controlled oscillators, power amplifiers, variable gain amplifiers, etc.</span></li>\r\n<li><span style=\"color: #3b3838; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 13.3333px;\">MmWave architects, systems and subsystems, such as receivers, transmitters, transceivers, phase-locked loops, frequency synthesisers, multistandard transceivers, digital radio, phased array beamformer, etc.</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"mso-margin-bottom-alt: auto; line-height: normal; mso-outline-level: 3; background: white;\"><strong><span style=\"font-size: 12.0pt; font-family: \'Arial\',sans-serif; mso-fareast-font-family: \'Times New Roman\'; color: black;\">Special Session Co-chairs:</span></strong></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"mso-margin-bottom-alt: auto; line-height: normal; background: white;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10.0pt; font-family: \'Arial\',sans-serif; mso-fareast-font-family: \'Times New Roman\'; color: black;\">Nguyen Ngoc Mai Khanh, The University of Tokyo, Japan</span></li>\r\n<li class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"mso-margin-bottom-alt: auto; line-height: normal; background: white;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10.0pt; font-family: \'Arial\',sans-serif; mso-fareast-font-family: \'Times New Roman\'; color: black;\">Huynh Phu Minh Cuong, Ho Chi Minh City University of Technology, Vietnam</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"mso-margin-bottom-alt: auto; line-height: normal; mso-outline-level: 3; background: white;\"><strong><span style=\"font-size: 12.0pt; font-family: \'Arial\',sans-serif; mso-fareast-font-family: \'Times New Roman\'; color: black;\">Submission:</span></strong></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"mso-margin-bottom-alt: auto; line-height: normal; background: white;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10.0pt; font-family: \'Arial\',sans-serif; mso-fareast-font-family: \'Times New Roman\'; color: black;\">All authors should prepare full versions of papers in Microsoft Word (DOC) or Portable Document Format (PDF). Papers must be limited to six pages, including text, references, tables, and figures &middot; All papers should be prepared according to the IEEE standard template. &middot; Submission link: https://www.edas.info/N29152</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"mso-margin-bottom-alt: auto; line-height: normal; mso-outline-level: 3; background: white;\"><strong><span style=\"font-size: 12.0pt; font-family: \'Arial\',sans-serif; mso-fareast-font-family: \'Times New Roman\'; color: black;\">Important Dates:</span></strong></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"mso-margin-bottom-alt: auto; line-height: normal; background: white;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10.0pt; font-family: \'Arial\',sans-serif; mso-fareast-font-family: \'Times New Roman\'; color: black;\">Extended submissions Deadline: <span style=\"color: #ff0000;\">April 08th, 2022 - </span></span><span style=\"color: #993300; text-decoration: line-through;\">Feb 28th , 2022</span></li>\r\n<li class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"mso-margin-bottom-alt: auto; line-height: normal; background: white;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10.0pt; font-family: \'Arial\',sans-serif; mso-fareast-font-family: \'Times New Roman\'; color: black;\">Acceptance Notification: <span style=\"color: #ff0000;\">May 30th, 2022</span></span></li>\r\n<li class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"mso-margin-bottom-alt: auto; line-height: normal; background: white;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10.0pt; font-family: \'Arial\',sans-serif; mso-fareast-font-family: \'Times New Roman\'; color: black;\">Camera-ready: <span style=\"color: #ff0000;\">June&nbsp;07th, 2022</span></span></li>\r\n<li class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"mso-margin-bottom-alt: auto; line-height: normal; background: white;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10.0pt; font-family: \'Arial\',sans-serif; mso-fareast-font-family: \'Times New Roman\'; color: black;\">Registration Deadline: <span style=\"color: #ff0000;\">June 10th, 2022</span></span></li>\r\n<li class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"mso-margin-bottom-alt: auto; line-height: normal; background: white;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10.0pt; font-family: \'Arial\',sans-serif; mso-fareast-font-family: \'Times New Roman\'; color: black;\">Conference Date:<span style=\"color: #ff0000;\"> July 27th &ndash; 29th , 2022</span></span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"mso-margin-bottom-alt: auto; line-height: normal; mso-outline-level: 3; background: white;\"><strong><span style=\"font-size: 12.0pt; font-family: \'Arial\',sans-serif; mso-fareast-font-family: \'Times New Roman\'; color: black;\">Publication:</span></strong></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"mso-margin-bottom-alt: auto; line-height: normal; background: white;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10.0pt; font-family: \'Arial\',sans-serif; mso-fareast-font-family: \'Times New Roman\'; color: black;\">All accepted papers will be published in the ICCE 2022 Conference Proceedings. Fully accepted papers will be forwarded to be published on IEEE Xplore&reg;.</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span style=\"font-family: \'Arial\',sans-serif;\">&nbsp;</span></p>', NULL, 'mmwave-technologies-and-circuits-for-rf-systems', NULL, NULL, 'PUBLISHED', 0, '2022-02-15 03:44:56', '2022-04-11 23:53:01');
